# Nalam schedule (times are container-local, TZ=Asia/Kolkata).
# Output goes to supercronic's stdout -> Docker logs -> Dozzle.
#
# Gemini key is shared with gajana (see CLAUDE.md); gajana's daily statement
# run fires at 06:00. Extraction runs earlier, at default (free-tier) pacing,
# so it never overlaps or starves gajana's run.

SHELL=/bin/sh

# Every 6 hours: Drive -> Paperless sync. No LLM calls, idempotent, cheap
# enough to run often so new scans get filed same-day.
0 */6 * * * cd /app && python run_sync.py

# Daily 04:30 IST: extract labs, discharge summaries and prescriptions from
# whatever's new since the last run (cached, idempotent). Radiology has no
# trusted extractor yet (see CLAUDE.md) so it stays manual.
30 4 * * * cd /app && python run_extract.py && python run_extract.py --discharge && python run_extract.py --prescriptions

# Weekly Sunday 05:00 IST: print medication-reconciliation diffs to the log
# for review. Read-only -- it never writes a decision on its own; that's
# always `run_meds.py --decide`, by a human.
0 5 * * 0 cd /app && python run_meds.py --reconcile

# Every minute: poll Telegram for incoming scans, file straight into
# Paperless. Cheap no-op when unconfigured (see run_telegram_bot.py).
* * * * * cd /app && python run_telegram_bot.py

# Every minute: drain the on-demand extraction queue a Telegram filing just
# added to (see run_extract_queue.py). Cheap no-op tick when the queue is
# empty -- still pushes a Paperless health heartbeat every tick regardless.
* * * * * cd /app && python run_extract_queue.py
